'''Bangladesh National Nutrition Council''' is an autonomous government body responsible for planning National Food and Nutrition Policy in Bangladesh and is located in Mohammadpur Thana, [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="nnv">{{cite web|last1=Mannan|first1=Mohammad Abdul|title=Bangladesh National Nutrition Council|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Bangladesh_National_Nutrition_Council|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=15 December 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Food import to double|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/food-import-double-1448695|accessdate=15 December 2017|work=The Daily Star|date=15 August 2017|language=en}}</ref> The council is chaired by the Prime Minister.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bangladesh rolls out a new action plan to combat malnutrition|url=https://bdnews24.com/health/2017/08/14/bangladesh-rolls-out-a-new-action-plan-to-combat-malnutrition|accessdate=15 December 2017|work=bdnews24.com}}</ref>
==History== Bangladesh National Nutrition Council was established in 1975 on the orders of the [[President of Bangladesh]]. Since 1998 the council observes National Nutrition Week every year at national, district, and upazila level. The council publishes a journal twice every year called the South Asian Journal of Nutrition. The council also helps plan nutritional nutrient programs for relevant seventeen ministries.<ref name="nnv"></ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Mahmud|first1=Iffat|last2=Mbuya|first2=Nkosinathi|title=Water, Sanitation, Hygiene, and Nutrition in Bangladesh: Can Building Toilets Affect Children's Growth?|date=2015|publisher=World Bank Publications|isbn=9781464806995|page=9|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dlz1CgAAQBAJ&pg=PA9&lpg=PA9&dq=Bangladesh+National+Nutrition+Council&source=bl&ots=SaoRQ1IYK9&sig=e3lcptxCj6gO99S3LjSU7IEwWIA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjKho3S_orYAhUJkeAKHZKmBSgQ6AEIlQEwFw#v=onepage&q=Bangladesh%20National%20Nutrition%20Council&f=false|language=en}}</ref> In 1994 with the help of the World Bank it carried out a national nutritional survey.<ref>{{cite news|title=Per head daily intake declined by 250 calories in 32 yrs|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news/per-head-daily-intake-declined-by-250-calories-in-32-yrs|accessdate=15 December 2017|work=The Daily Star|date=1 August 1997|language=en}}</ref>
